Sunny- N winds at 10mph.  Carp spawn.
Sunny- winds are west at 10-15 mph.  Heavy rain last night.
Three days of fairly heavy rain this past week.  Also very windy today.
Dry weather but opening day of duck.  Lots of particles floating.  Maybe hunters in and out of marsh area.
Lake level 10-12" higher than norm- big runoff problems 6 days prior due to heavy rain- ice off 3 weeks prior.
Third week after heavy rains.  The lake is the clearest I've seen in years.  Calm and sunny.  Some floating masses of green .
Fairly calm today- but extremely windy the previous 3 days.  Still nice and clear along the shoreline to 8 ft depth.
Cool- windy- suspended algae- medium boat traffic
High winds + rain early this a.m.- cool temps.
Week of above average rains- increased boat traffic for 4th of July weekend
Continued period of above average rainfall- increased visibility of suspended algae particles
Very warm- sunny- above average boat traffic today
Very hot + humid- no wind the past 4 days
Air temp 70's- light boat traffic- hot + humid this past week
Heavy rains yesterday am.  Lake level is up.  Sunny today- moderate wind- 70 degrees.
Cooler weather.  Noticeable drop in water level due to lowering of dam.  Shallower water seems to be clearing up faster.
Although secchi reading is 1 foot more- there are blooms and scum across surface.  Cool rainy weather this past week.
Very windy these past few days.  Weather is warmer than the last few weeks.  Difficult to get a good reading.  Lake is riled up.
Cool and windy the past few days.  Partly sunny- cool and light wind today.  No improvement in clarity.
Floating green algae blooms all week.
Green layer near shoreline these past few weeks.  Also foam on the shore.  Today was the greenest we've noticed.  Cool- sunny- light wind today- 40 degrees.
Ice off March 22nd.  Definite brown color.  Heavy winds past few weeks.
Still brownish color.  No noticeable improvement in clarity yet.  Calm- sunny.
Warm- sunny- visible signs of clearing in shallow waters.
Slightly overcast- calm.  Increase in weed density in most areas of lake noted.  Water clarity improving.
Partly cloudy - no rain last few weeks.  Heavy boat traffic over weekend.
Sunny- calm.  Many more weeds noticeable in many parts of lake.  Growing to surface.
Windy- sunny- 90 degrees- increase in lake weeds noticed
Heavy boat traffic over the weekend.  Windy- sunny- hot.  Secchi only for this date- no chemistry data.
Increased suspended (small) algae noticeable- more weeds noticed.
Lots of algae blooms appearing.  Lake has smell of fish.
Not as many noticeable floating algae.  Sunny- calm- deeper green color.
Cool- cloudy- windy- 4/10" of rain yesterday
Hot- sunny.  Lake lowered for past 5 days 4'.  Lots of weeds.
Windy the past weekend- overcast- tiny creatures seen in van Dorn at the lower levels.  Substantial amount of algae in shallower waters
One month past ice off- fairly windy.  Cool temps this spring so far- temp is 50 degrees and sunny.
Sunny- windy.  Assumed sample was taken at noon.
Sunny- increasing boat traffic.  Some algae blooms noted in shallower water.
Sunny- water looks great!  no weeds yet- warm.
Sunny- high boat traffic.  Floating suspended green particles seen.
Hot- sunny- heavy boat traffic all weekend.
Overcast- calm- high boat traffic this past weekend.  Lots of floating/suspended green fragments (algae  chopped up weeds )
High boat traffic all week- sunny- 80 degrees.
Sunny- windy.  No large particles seen- but overall clarity is low-green cast.
Sunny- calm- green scum noted along shore this a.m.
Sunny- windy- lots of rain/run-off past 7 days.
Sunny- cool- lots of algae noticed.  Back bay is very choked with that floating algae.
Partly cloudy- cool.  Water level: up 4"
Lots of rain this month. lots of weeds at 8-10' depth. sunny- calm.
Chopped up weeds from heavy weekend boat traffic.  Sunny- calm- more weeds this summer than we've seen for years.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 3'.
Outside of loads of weeds on + around shore + bays- pretty good for this time of year.
Sunny- calm- noticeable weeds chopped up from boat traffic all over shorelines.
Great clarity for august. only problem is weeds chopped + free-floating from lake traffic. sunny- calm.

Some blooms- becoming noticeable now. sunny- cool.
Partly sunny.  Light northeast wind.  Drizzle most of yesterday.
Some algae in shallower depths. calm sunny and saw 2 loons.

Lake cleared up all of a sudden!
5 1/2 inches of rain 2 weeks ago- lots of weeds.
Calm and cool.  Algae on the surface.
Medium SE wind- sunny- 65 F- warm past weekend- lots of boat traffic already.
Partly cloudy- 70 F- light SW wind- lots of weeds- lots of rain this month.
Sunny- NE wind- warm past few weeks- high surface water temp.

Sunny- 65 degrees.  Lake level up slightly
Sunny- 60 degrees- lots of rain in the past few weeks.
Lots of aquatic plants growing and chopped up by high volume boat traffic
Lake high- lots of rain this week- lots of aquatic plants.
Sunny- very windy- very rainy last 6 weeks.  Lots of aquatic plants.
Partly sunny and cloudy.  Lots of algae- lake quite green.
Sunny- calm- lots of rain past few weeks.
Sunny- medium to heavy winds- and cool.
Sunny- light wind- and the weeds are very thick!
12 baby ducks- 5 blue heron- lots of weeds/algae blooms- sunny and warm.
Sunny and heavy boat traffic past few days.
Partly cloudy and the nights are getting cooler.
Partly sunny. Baby geese observed two days ago
Sunny- light wind.  Lots of weeds!
Cloudy today.  One inch of rain the past 24 hours.
Overcast today.  Very windy this morning.
Calm- sunny.  Heavy- heavy boat traffic this month.

Sunny- cool today.   Overall the summer observations were of lots of weeds- lots of boat traffic- esp. pricy- larger-sized boats making a larger wake.  Also construction of 40-lot subdivision underway the past year within one-third mile of lake.

column2: COOL- OVERCAST- BIG MARSH FIRE 2 DAYS AGO! 150 ACRES BURNED.  Loons arrived March 13.
Sunny- calm.  Dead carp noted around lake.  80 F.  Beautiful day.
Still a few dead carp noticed.  Large die-off in early August!  Just carp.
Sunny- ice off April 1.  40 loons on April 4th.  Light wind.  60s.
Cloudy- light wind.  Hot- dry summer.  Weeds not as invasive as last year- but more boat traffic than ever!
Sunny- calm.  Low lake levels this summer.
Water appears clear- but clumps of green--blooms from trees or lake
Weeds are the thickest that they've ever been out in front of our property- the past 18 years.  Water green! Sunny- calm.
Sunny- calm day.  Lots of green blooms on the north end of the lake--a bright- light green.
80- sunny- calm- lake surface-green algae. 4 adolescent mute swans.
Sunny- calm- floating chunks--algae   Quite a few dead catfish noticed around the lake the past week- mostly around 12".
Clumps of algae noticed again the past few days.  Wind took it away today.
Sunny- calm- lake green.  August and September boat traffic noticeably less.  Weed killing done in June and July seemed to make a difference in boating/skiing on most of the lake.
Sunny- calm- 60 F.  Weed spraying done.
Lake has middle-of-summer smell already.  Decaying weeds from spraying last month possibly
Sunny today. 1" of rain 36 hours ago.  Weeds on north end of lake have popped up again.
sunny- warm- second hatching of ducklings July 15 in my flower bed.  Disturbing discovery on one of our shoreline rocks--zebra mussel!  First we've ever seen.
Lake has cleared up now- but north end and east shore were very brown from runoff (new subdivision development on NE end)from last week's heavy rains.

We found a dozen good-size zebra mussels on bottom of our pier wheel when we pulled it.  This was very disappointing- as the testing we've been doing with the DNR the past years and earlier this summer failed to show signs of these things in their earliest stages--velligers--though we knew it would happen.  Bar/launch (Dooley's) closed mid summer and we noticed a substantial decrease in boat/jet ski traffic on the weekends.
Sunny- 60- calm.Brown algae clumps.  Ice out 4/5/08.  14 loons spotted 4/6/08 on patch of open water- but now there's just a few left.
Partly sunny- windy- weeds have been controlled this year in spite of heavy rains earlier.
Partly cloudy- warm.  Weeds still well controlled.  Veligers noted on traps set under our pier!

Sunny- warm- a beautiful fall day.  Pulled out boat lifts and parts of piers.  Boat lift loaded with zebra mussels.  Last year we had 10 total maybe on the tires of our pier (bottom that sits on lake bed).  This fall we have 10-000!  Last few months the clarity of shallower water on our swimming beach area has appeared noticeably clearer.

Clear- calm- cool. Ice off February 22 in 70 degree weather.

Cool- partly cloudy- light wind. LAKE finally starting to get a little clearer.

column2: Sunny- cool. Weeds are down thanks to weed cutting in July and August.
Sunny- clear- light wind. 80 and humid. Lots of thick weeds and boating traffic over the weekend. Trumpeter swans observed first time! On conservancy bay.

Cloudy- light wind- 80. Very prolific mute swan hatch this spring- more families than ever. No trumpeters on our main body of water and weeds too thick on conservancy bay to see if they're still there.

Sunnyy- hot-light wind. Lake temp overall 2 degrees warmer than last year. More wakeboard boats on lake than ever seen- and jet skiers jumping their wakes! First fatality 2 days ago- jet ski vs. Jet boat. We are maxxed out on boat traffic most summer days!
